My father has served in defence forces which has inculcated in me the ability to mould myself according to the circumstances. My mother is a home maker and she has imbibed in me the qualities which help in striking perfect balance between personal and professional life. My brother is working in a bank and my sister is married. I love my family and they mean a lot to me. They have always been there for me and I am sure I will be there for them too. 

I work as a gazzeted officer with state government currently posted at Samba. I enjoy working as it provides a new face and direction to my life. I like my job and I feel proud doing it. I am sure I will excel in whatever field I go because patience and perseverance always pays.

In leisure time, I watch television and read good books. While travelling I enjoy listening to melodious old songs. I am a keen observer of nature and enjoy exploring my surroundings.,"The man I get married to can be from any profession as I do not judge people by what they do for their living. I describe myself as a simple and soft spoken girl. I give utmost importance to family values in my life and follow them.
I am a hard working individual and do all my work with great determination. Presently I am working as a teacher in a government school. In future I would like to pursue my career in the same field and attain a reputed position in life. 
My main weakness is that I am very emotional due to which many people take advantage of me. I am trying to overcome my emotional nature. 
My mother is no more and father is a retired food inspector. I have two lovely sisters who are happily married and a brother who is currently working as a regional Manager in a Pharmaceutical Company. 
In the higher education sector I have completed BA (English) from MLKPG College, MA (English) LBSPG College, B Ed from Saket College and P hd English from DAV College Dehradun.
There are very few friends in my life and I like to be with them and share my feelings and thoughts with them. Further, in my free time I like to do cooking, watch TV, listen to music and read books.,"I am looking for a simple and down to earth man to enter my life. He should give importance to the family values. He should also respect our cultural and traditional values and must give them importance. I want him to accept my family and adjust with them. In return he will also seek a lot of love and respect from my family members.

I have no choices regarding the profession of my husband but he should be well settled. If he is well settled then in future we will have no problems in our life. I would personally prefer marrying a man from UP (Uttar Pradesh). My life partner should be a well educated person with a broader perspective in judging and analyzing life. He should be mature enough to understand the importance of marriage and must be ready for a life time committed relation. Further, he must belong to a decent family background and should have a good image in the society.
I am ready to give all my love to him if he is like the one I am looking for.

column1:
An open-minded person knows how to take things in a positive way. He takes everything in good humor. They dona??t mind what people say and dona??t take things very seriously even if they are weird. I am one of those people and I know how to get over negative things. 
I have been the same since childhood. My parents taught me how to be open-minded. This has not only helped me in remaining happy but has also helped me in getting in the good books of many people I like. Being open-minded has always been an advantage for me.
Professionally, I am a Software engineer in an MNC and I love my job a lot. I enjoy every bit of it. In future, I would like to stick to the same field and excel in it. 
I have always been a very sincere student. After schooling, I did graduation in B Com and post graduation in MCA from Pune.
I am a person who values her family a lot and I also give credit for my success to my family. They are the ones without whom I wouldna??t have been able to reach this far. My mother is a homemaker and my father is a Business man. I have one sister and she is happily married into a reputed family. 
I like writing poems and I feel very lucky that I can express my feelings in this form. Apart from that, I like to read books and do photography.,"The man I get married to must be well qualified and educated as I value education a lot and feel that it is all because of education that a person knows how to behave properly in front of others. This is why being educated is a priority for me.

When two people get married then a relation is formed not only between those two people but also between their families, therefore, I want that the family I get married into should be very good natured. This will not only make me but also my family very happy.

He should be very kind at heart and loving, as any girl would like to expect all this in her partner. I will be able to adjust easily if he is like this and if he accepts me with all his love and respect.

I believe a lot in showing mutual respect and love for one another. I expect my partner to be very respectful towards me and I will have the same feelings for him as well. He should not only respect me but my profession and my habits too. This way we can become an ideal couple.

I am very modern as a person so he can feel at ease with me. This will avoid many problems between us. I am sure if he is also modern then we can become a wonderful couple. He can trust me with the household work but I will need his help at times.

I respect the idea of a good friend in a husband. I will love it if he becomes a good friend of mine as I will feel more connected to him this way.","Father-Kokanastha brahmin.age68, retired from statePWD as Secretary to Govt.now practicing actively as consulting Engineer.

My personality reflects my simple and calm nature. I speak softly and generally stay patient in life and it helps me in maintaining friendly relations with everyone. Further, I am a hard working individual working with an aim to make my parents feel proud of me.

Both my parents are responsible Doctors of the society and I have a brother as well who is working as a Consultant in US. I love my family as they are my greatest power and I can do anything to make them happy. 
In my higher education sector I have completed MBBS from KMC Manipal and MS from Bangalore. 
Life brings a lot of unexpected people in our life who give us immense happiness. In my life I have very few people as my friends but they are the most eminent part of my life. column1: It is quite difficult to write about oneself but I would like to begin by saying what I feel about the institution of marriage. I feel that without mutual trust everything else including love is futile in any relationship and trust is what I would expect from my partner. I strongly believe in gender equality and would expect my partner to take as much responsibility of me and my parents and family as he would expect from me. I am a career oriented person and have well decided goals for my future. I am very clear in mind that I would not settle abroad for any reason whatsoever. I love to travel though and have varied interests which include photography and recently gardening. Like any other woman I also enjoy doing home decor and love to collect rare or delicate art works from the places I travel to. I have traveled both in India as well as abroad and believe in taking two trips per year, one for travel within India and one abroad. I am not too spiritual but believe god exists in every little thing that we see around us. I feel there is magic all around us we just need to open our hearts to it, i also strongly feel that whatever happens is for the good and for a purpose which we may or may not understand. I hope to meet someone with an open heart and broad mind, who can love and trust his spouse and treat her with respect and accept her the way she is, for what she is and give her the wings to fly to the moon, and its quite simple if you could just love and trust her.,,,,20 Apr 1977,18:30:00,India,Nagpur,Average,,,Goswami,,Mumbai,,Fair ,,Self,MD/ MS (Medicine),"36 yrs, 5ft 2in,

Hi -Searching for a very specific type of guy. My sister is a very adventurous yet kind hearted person. She has grown up in both an Eastern and Western environment and is a perfect amalgam of the two cultures. She understands the need for tradition when it is appropriate but leads a very Australian lifestyle on a day to day basis. She is highly intelligent and extremely athletic. Guys interested in her would need to appreciate these qualities. She appreciates good intelligent conversation as well as the ability to cut loose and have a wild, crazy and fun time. A good and quirky sense of humour is a definite must in any potential partner. She loves adventure sports and travelling the world and you must enjoy this as well. Rock Climbing, Snow skiing and Martial Arts are her particular fortes having reached the pinnacle in all of these but she will try most things even if just for a laugh. When not travelling the world, (she has done everything from diving with great Whites to Everest Base Camp) she is found at home cooking up a storm or baby sitting her niece and nephew who totally adore her. She enjoys the company of her numerous ecclectic friends and easily fits into any social situation or group. Her ideal partner should be willing to share her life adventures with her and indeed introduce her to many and more fun times. Life after all is meant to be for living!He should be extremely loyal to her as she will be to him. A high ethical and moral standard is a must. She/We do not believe in the cast system or any such social yoke so if you are into that or dates of birth or horoscopes etc then she is not the girl for you. She is looking for an equal or better so if you are looking for a "fair", "traditional girl" with good" homely values" then again she is not the girl for you. She respects and ascribes to all of these naturally, but is not constrained by that mindset. If you are looking for an attractive, athletic girl with an awesome sense of humour who loves living life to the full and extracting every moment of joy that she can, If you want an equal in life and not someone subserviant then she is certainly the type for you. all profiles with pics or emails with pics included will be replied to - and pending further discussion we will also reply with photos.,,,28 to 40,24 Oct 1977,,Australia,,Athletic,Doesn't Matter,,Hindu-Others,,Others,,Dark ,Doesn't Matter,Sister,LLB,"36 yrs, 5ft 6in,

column1:
I am 32, single, Hindu female living in Hyderabad.

I completed my Post Graduation in Commerce. 

A smart, Outgoing, Loving, Caring, emotional Person. 
I am an outgoing person at the same time composed and sensitive. 
Get emotional at times but know how to handle difficult situations with equal ease. 
I have a very closed knit friends circle who are very special and valuable to me, I value their support and contribution to what I am today. 
I am a very family person inspite of being a workaholic, love spending time at home watching televsion, movies with my family. 
I believe in the quote 'Nothing succeeds like success'. 
Ethics and values are quite imp. in a person which makes up one's personality and identity. 
I am quite pleasing by nature, love having loads of fun and frolic. 
As a working girl I would want to continue working with duly respecting the exceptions which might come on my way.,"I need a person in my life who is loving, caring, humorous, intellectual, pleasing to my eye, with a sense of style and who is family orientated too. An optimistic individual with a positive outlook to life. Someone who likes books, nature, movies. Someone who is patient, liberal and not very judgmental.
